  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Uncertainty quantification was performed via Latin hypercube sampling across blood viscosity, inlet flow rate, rotational speed, and gap tolerances; a screening sensitivity study using elementary-effects (Morris) method was conducted internally and referenced in the UQ report narrative. Uncertainty bounds on the relative hemolysis index (RH) remain within acceptable margins at all five operating points.",
