      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions documented and traceable; inlet flow and rotational speed match COU operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "FDA experimental dataset provides fully characterized boundary conditions: inlet flow rates 2.5–6.0 L/min, rotational speeds 2000–3500 RPM, fluid temperature 37 ± 0.5 °C, hematocrit 33 ± 1%. All five COU operating points fall within the validated experimental envelope. Traceability to NIST-calibrated instrumentation confirmed."
