      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH is the primary regulatory QoI per FDA guidance on blood-contacting devices. RH < 1 acceptance criterion directly maps to the predicate device comparison required for 510(k) submission. Secondary QoIs (shear stress distribution, residence time) support mechanistic understanding and are consistent with the Giersiepen power-law hemolysis model employed."
