      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 provided model form is consistent with validation evidence.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-ω turbulence model and Giersiepen hemolysis power-law are standard choices for CFD hemolysis prediction, consistent with published FDA guidance and peer-reviewed literature. Formal model form uncertainty quantification is not required at MRL 2. Factor recorded as not-assessed per MRL 2 sufficiency table."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Key model inputs documented with sources; uncertainty ranges specified for inputs subject to manufacturing variability.",
      "rationale": "All model inputs documented: fluid density (1060 kg/m³ ± 1%), viscosity (0.0035 Pa·s ± 3%), inlet velocity profile (derived from flow meter ± 2%), rotational speed (± 10 RPM), and five geometric tolerance parameters (gap height, impeller diameter, volute clearance, blade angle, diffuser width) with ± 2σ manufacturing tolerances from CMM measurements. UQ report documents input distributions and references an internal screening sensitivity study (Morris elementary-effects method, r=10 trajectories, 13 input factors) that identified viscosity, rotational speed, and gap height as the top contributors to RH variance. Structured sensitivity analysis linkage is captured in the UQ narrative documentation."
    },
    {
